# Installation Guide

***

## Package Configuration
### Modules
To install the project's required dependencies, copy the following command and paste it in the terminal:
> npm install bcrypt connect-sqlite3 dotenv ejs express express-session jsonwebtoken multer path socket.io socket.io-client sqlite3
This should create package.json and package-lock.json files. 

### Initializing the Database
In order to initialize your project's database, you *need* to add the following to your package.json file:
>    "scripts": {
>        "init-database": "node scripts/initDatabase.js",
>    }
To initialize your database, run the following command in your terminal:
> npm run init-database

#### Optional Package Configuration
Optionally, you may edit the package.json file to include the corret name, description, main, author, and license.

***

Once you have completed all the steps outlined above, your package.json file should look something like this:
> {
>    "name": "your_project_name",
>    "description": "your_description",
>    "main": "app.js",
>    "author": "your_name",
>    "license": "your_license" ,
>    "scripts": {
>        "init-database": "node scripts/initDatabase.js",
>    },
>    "dependencies": {
>        "bcrypt": "^6.0.0",
>        "connect-sqlite3": "^0.9.16",
>        "dotenv": "^17.2.3",
>        "ejs": "^3.1.10",
>        "express": "^5.2.1",
>        "express-session": "^1.18.2",
>        "jsonwebtoken": "^9.0.3",
>        "multer": "^2.0.2",
>        "path": "^0.12.7",
>        "socket.io": "^4.8.1",
>        "socket.io-client": "^4.8.1",
>        "sqlite3": "^5.1.7"
>    },
> }

***

## Templates
### Environment Variables
Copy the .env_template file. Rename it to .env. Configure your port, session secret, Formbar API key and redirect path, and your uploads and database directories.

### gitignore
Copy the .gitignore_template file. Rename it to .gitignore. Configure your data directories, and add any additional files you'd like to ignore.

*** 

## Starting the Server
After the server has been properly configured as outlined above, start the server with the following command:
> node app.js